The paper deals with coding schemes for wire-tap and broadcast channels, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-fields of computer science. The use of stochastic encoding and the trade-off between different message rates suggest a focus on coding theory and communication systems, which are also covered in cs.MM (multimedia) and cs.SI (signal processing). Finally, the paper's emphasis on security and optimization aligns with the topics covered in cs.LG (machine learning).
